history.text: Hello, how are you today?
Im doing fine.
Have you seen Home Alone?
Yes I have.
Did you ever saw it?
Bring back many happy childhood memories-grew up watching it, over and over again!
especially around Christmas!
Macaulay Culkin was still a normal kid back then
Really? I saw the film as a kid too. I actually had a little crush on Macaulay Caulkin!
Yes:-), he was still normal back then!
Yes he were. Unfortunately Hollywood did him in.
such an innocent movie that reminds me of the good old 80's decade
such a peaceful time!
It was a very cute and sweet film, they don't make them like that anymore
It sure were@ I loved Joe Pesci's character. it was funny. So was Daniel Stern
yes, totally!
Yeah the film was such a classic and I think the entire cast was great.
They made modern version of the movie-not the same at all! Today everything has to be " boom doom and gloom!"
zombies and apocalypse!
Yes, all the actors were phenomenal !
I were about to mention that. Yes its true about today's film. Too much end of the world type movies makes you feel will  become a zombie yourself lol
I know, that's why I always re-watch the oldies-like this one!
Even my kids liked Home Alone, although they think it is ancient!:=)
Hey, it might be ancient but like I said earlier, it's a classic just like Miracle on 34th street. It never gets old.
Very true!
What's your favorite part of the movie?
I love when he fights the two villains, but the best and most touching part is when he gets reunited with his parents!
Yes! and his cousin butch. He was such a bully to him. I like it when Kevin saw a picture of his girlfriend and said yuck! lol
Yes, Butch was funny!
and the two nerdy cousins with glasses:-)
He is a very smart boy and knew how to set up booby traps for those villains too
yes, very imaginative!
And the old man that was shoveling the snow that he was initially afraid of!
Very touching story there!
I wondered why the entire family did not head back home. Only the mom did. I dont think i could be comfortable on the other side of the world with my young  family member at home by himself;
I forgot about the old man. He did came across as creepy but was definitely sincere and helped him out at the end.
oh and John candy was in in too
That's true-but I guess mother was the first person who would want to be with him!
John Candy was an awesome comedian, rest his soul! so many good films!
It worked out at the end so that what matters
Yes!
Have a great day and thanks for the chat!
I am glad to have this conversation with you
Thanks and you're welcome

uid2response.feedback: Great partner and very polite, thanks so much!
